net.markenwerk.commons.iterators

Interface ProtectedIterator<Payload>

  • Type Parameters:
    Payload - The payload type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterator<Payload>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayIterator, BooleanArrayIterator, ByteArrayIterator, CharacterArrayIterator, CountDownIterator, CountUpIterator, DoubleArrayIterator, EmptyIterator, EnumerationIterator, FloatArrayIterator, IntegerArrayIterator, LongArrayIterator, LookAheadIterator, ObjectIterator, OptionalIterator, ProtectingIterator, ShortArrayIterator, StringTokenizerIterator

    public interface ProtectedIterator<Payload>
extends Iterator<Payload>
    A ProtectedIterator is an Iterator that guarantees that every call to Iterator.remove() throws an UnsupportedOperationException and doesn't alter the underlying data.

    ProtectedIterator is a marker interface.

    Since:
    1.2.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)
